<div class="heading resPageHeading">


























<h1 >Personal Information Banks</h1></div>

<div class="content stackparsys">










				
				<div class="resText parbase section">


























<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="f9b93fc4-57fe-4d48-abe9-3b9c7a1d8986" >

    <h1><strong>September 2014<br> </strong></h1> 
<p>All records containing personal information are retained for at least one year under the Freedom of Information and Protection of Privacy Act. Longer retention periods may be in force pursuant to Ryerson University's&nbsp;<a href="/content/ryerson/policies/policy-list/records-policy.html">Records Management Policy</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href="/content/ryerson/gcbs/what-we-do/records/records-retention.html">Records Retention Schedule (RRS)</a>.<br> </p> 
<p>The Personal information banks below are organized according to the 11 Functions described in Ryerson's Records Retention Schedule.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br> </p>
    





</div>
<script>$(document).ready(function(){addCoursePopover("#f9b93fc4-57fe-4d48-abe9-3b9c7a1d8986");});</script></div>

				

				
				<div class="resText parbase section">


























<div class="res-text richtextContent background-opaque" id="5f67354e-d607-443b-b43f-a90603863873" >

    <h2>Administration</h2> 
<h3><em><strong>General Counsel</strong></em></h3> 
<ul> 
 <li><strong>Location</strong>: General Counsel</li> 
 <li><strong>Legal Authority</strong>:&nbsp;<em>Ryerson University Act</em>, 1977 (amended)</li> 
 <li><strong>Information Maintained</strong>: name, phone number, home address, personal contact information, opinion, evaluative material in connection with legal files or Freedom of Information request files</li> 
 <li><strong>Uses</strong>: to provide legal advice and in the case of Freedom of Information files, to respond to requests, communicate with requesters, respond to breaches and privacy complaints&nbsp;<strong>Users</strong>: General Counsel</li> 
 <li><strong>Individuals in Bank</strong>: students, staff, faculty, contractors, members of the public</li> 
 <li><strong>Retention and Disposal</strong>:&nbsp;<strong>TBD</strong></li> 
</ul>
    





</div>
<script>$(document).ready(function(){addCoursePopover("#5f67354e-d607-443b-b43f-a90603863873");});</script></div>

				

				
				<div class="resText parbase section">


























<div class="res-text richtextContent background-opaque" id="0806b678-6119-4ae9-b7c2-0009c5b41ab3" >

    <h2>Campus Services<br> </h2> 
<h3><em><strong>Campus Services</strong></em></h3> 
<ul> 
 <li><strong>Location</strong>: One Card Office, Parking Office, Bookstore, Conference Services and Ryerson Theatre/Facilities Rental</li> 
 <li><strong>Legal Authority</strong>:&nbsp;<em>Ryerson University Act</em>, 1977 (amended)</li> 
 <li><strong>Information Maintained</strong>: 
  <ul> 
   <li><strong></strong>In all locations - name, home address, home telephone number, student number, employee number;</li> 
   <li><strong></strong>In parking services - license plate information, ownership information, health information related to requests for special needs parking, year of program;</li> 
   <li><strong></strong>In the One Card Office – photograph; and</li> 
   <li><strong></strong>In the Bookstore – credit card information and other payment information and purchases made</li> 
  </ul> </li> 
 <li><strong>Users</strong>: One Card Office, Parking Services, Bookstore, Conference Services and Ryerson Theatre/Facilities Rental, as applicable</li> 
 <li><strong>Uses</strong>: to maintain records of parking permits issued, One Card registration, Bookstore purchases, conference and other Ryerson University facility bookings</li> 
 <li><strong>Individuals in Bank:&nbsp;</strong>students, faculty and staff</li> 
 <li><strong>Retention and Disposal</strong>:&nbsp;<strong>3-7 years</strong></li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3><strong><em>Mattamy Athletic Centre (MAC), Ryerson Athletic Centre (RAC) [See also Student Services - Sports and Recreation]</em></strong></h3> 
<ul> 
 <li><strong>Location:&nbsp;</strong>MAC, RAC</li> 
 <li><strong>Legal Authority:&nbsp;</strong><em>Ryerson University Act</em>, 1977 (amended)</li> 
 <li><strong>Information Maintained:&nbsp;</strong>membership forms, name, contact information, emergency contact information, limited health information</li> 
 <li><strong>Uses</strong>: to operate and maintain memberships of RAC&nbsp;</li> 
 <li><strong>Users</strong>: RAC staff and emergency contacts if necessary</li> 
 <li><strong>Individuals in Bank</strong>: students, staff and members of public<br> </li> 
 <li><strong>Retention and Disposal</strong>:&nbsp;<strong>5 years</strong></li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3><em><strong>Ryerson Early Learning Centre (day care centre)</strong></em></h3> 
<ul> 
 <li><strong>Location</strong>: Ryerson Early Learning Centre</li> 
 <li><strong>Legal Authority:&nbsp;</strong><em>Ryerson University Act</em>, 1977 (amended),&nbsp;<em>Day Nurseries Act</em></li> 
 <li><strong>Information Maintained</strong>: name, date of birth, address, telephone number, parent name and business telephone, doctor's name and address, child's medical history and immunization record, permission forms (video and photographic records of child, administration of medication, participation on excursions), child's schedule and behaviour patterns</li> 
 <li><strong>Uses</strong>: to document registration, activities and development of child in daycare program, facilitate daily and emergency care</li> 
 <li><strong>Users</strong>: Early Learning Centre staff and emergency contacts if necessary</li> 
 <li><strong>Individuals in Bank</strong>: students, staff and members of public</li> 
 <li><strong>Retention and Disposal</strong>:&nbsp;<strong>5 years</strong></li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3><em><strong>Ryerson University Day Camp</strong></em></h3> 
<ul> 
 <li><strong>Location</strong>: Student Services – Sports and Recreation</li> 
 <li><strong>Legal Authority:&nbsp;</strong><em>Ryerson University Act</em>, 1977 (amended)</li> 
 <li><strong>Information Maintained</strong>: name, date of birth, address, telephone number, parent name and business telephone, doctor's name and address, child's medical history and immunization record, permission forms (video and photographic records of child, administration of medication, participation on excursions), emergency contact information, OHIP number</li> 
 <li><strong>Uses</strong>: to maintain records of campers and ensure proper care while enrolled in day camp program</li> 
 <li><strong>Users</strong>: Sports and Recreation staff, day camp staff</li> 
 <li><strong>Individuals in Bank</strong>: campers</li> 
 <li><strong>Retention and Disposal</strong>:&nbsp;<strong>5 years</strong></li> 
</ul>
    





</div>
<script>$(document).ready(function(){addCoursePopover("#0806b678-6119-4ae9-b7c2-0009c5b41ab3");});</script></div>

				

				
				<div class="resText parbase section">


























<div class="res-text richtextContent background-opaque" id="3a752122-498a-4129-8201-6df6aeee81ee" >

    <h2>External Relations and Communications</h2> 
<h3><strong><em>Convocation/Alumni Records</em></strong></h3> 
<ul> 
 <li><strong>Location</strong>: University Advancement</li> 
 <li><strong>Legal Authority</strong>:&nbsp;<em>Ryerson University Act</em>, 1977 (amended)</li> 
 <li><strong>Information Maintained</strong>: name, sex, date of birth, telephone, email, parents names and addresses, program and graduation information, student activities, further education, donations, gifts, employment status and description</li> 
 <li><strong>Uses</strong>: to maintain a record of alumni for contact and communications and fundraising purposes</li> 
 <li><strong>Users</strong>: University Advancement staff</li> 
 <li><strong>Individuals in Bank:&nbsp;</strong>alumni</li> 
 <li><strong>Retention and Disposal: Indefinitely</strong></li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3><em><strong>Donor Files and Agreements</strong></em></h3> 
<ul> 
 <li><strong>Location</strong>: University Advancement</li> 
 <li><strong>Legal Authority</strong>:&nbsp;<em>Ryerson University Act</em>, 1977 (amended)</li> 
 <li><strong>Information Maintained</strong>: name, sex, date of birth, telephone, email, donations, gifts, employment status and description, educational history, financial history, correspondence regarding donations with Ryerson University, internal reports regarding donations.</li> 
 <li><strong>Uses</strong>: to maintain a record of donations/contacts and agreements entered into between</li> 
 <li>Ryerson University and donors</li> 
 <li><strong>Users</strong>: University Advancement staff</li> 
 <li><strong>Individuals in Bank</strong>: donors and potential donors</li> 
 <li><strong>Retention and Disposal</strong>:&nbsp;<strong>Indefinitely</strong></li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3><strong><em>Honourary Degrees</em></strong></h3> 
<ul> 
 <li><strong>Location</strong>: the Office of the Secretary of Senate</li> 
