<ul> 
 <li><strong>Location</strong>: 
  <ul> 
   <li><strong>Academic Misconduct</strong>: the Office of the Secretary of Senate (third level appeals), applicable faculties and departments, Academic Integrity Office (first level suspected misconduct), Office of the Registrar (if misconduct is found)</li> 
   <li><strong>Non-Academic Misconduct</strong>: the Office of the Secretary of Senate if matter is escalated from the Director of Student Services or if withdrawal or expulsion has been determined appropriate by the Director of Student Services</li> 
  </ul> </li> 
 <li><strong>Legal Authority</strong>:&nbsp;<em>Ryerson University Act</em>, 1977 (amended)</li> 
 <li><strong>Information Maintained</strong>: name, home contact information, student number, educational history, student’s personal opinions, opinions from faculty and the Director of Student Services (in the case of non-academic misconduct) about the student, notes, memorandums and disciplinary action taken</li> 
 <li><strong>Uses</strong>: to maintain records of student academic and non-academic misconduct and to maintain aggregated statistical records</li> 
 <li><strong>Users</strong>: faculty and department staff, Office of the Registrar and Senate Appeals</li> 
 <li>Committee, the Office of the Secretary of Senate</li> 
 <li><strong>Individuals in Bank</strong>: students involved in academic or non-academic discipline and misconduct matters</li> 
 <li><strong>Retention and Disposal</strong>:&nbsp;<strong>Indefinitely</strong></li> 
