 <li><strong>Uses:&nbsp;</strong>to assist student transition to Ryerson University and to assist with study and general management techniques</li> 
 <li><strong>Users:&nbsp;</strong>Learning Success Centre staff</li> 
 <li><strong>Individuals in Bank:&nbsp;</strong>students</li> 
 <li><strong>Retention and Disposal: 5 years</strong></li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3><em><strong>Mature Students</strong></em></h3> 
<ul> 
 <li><strong>Location:&nbsp;</strong>Student Services – Mature Students</li> 
 <li><strong>Legal Authority:&nbsp;</strong><em>Ryerson University Act</em>, 1977 (amended)</li> 
 <li><strong>Information Maintained:&nbsp;</strong>student name, number, contact information, program of study&nbsp;</li> 
 <li><strong>Uses:&nbsp;</strong>to support decisions related to program planning and development, report and professional training</li> 
 <li><strong>Users:&nbsp;</strong>Mature Student staff&nbsp;<strong><br> </strong></li> 
 <li><strong>Individuals in Bank:&nbsp;</strong>students</li> 
 <li><strong>Retention and Disposal: 5 years</strong></li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3><em><strong>Sports and Recreation</strong></em></h3> 
<ul> 
 <li><strong>Location</strong>: Student Services - Mattamy Athletic Centre (MAC), Ryerson Athletic Center (RAC)</li> 
 <li><strong>Legal Authority</strong>:&nbsp;<em>Ryerson University Act</em>, 1977 (amended)</li> 
 <li><strong>Information Maintained</strong>: name, contact information, emergency contact information, limited health information, in the case of varsity and intramural sports – age, weight, hometown, year and program of study</li> 
 <li><strong>Uses</strong>: to operate and manage the RAC and its membership base, keep track of student participation in organized sports, advance varsity and intramural student sport participation and awareness within the university community</li> 
 <li><strong>Users</strong>: RAC, Student Services</li> 
 <li><strong>Individuals in Bank</strong>: students, staff and Ryerson community members who are members of RAC</li> 
 <li><strong>Retention and Disposal</strong>:&nbsp;<strong>5 years</strong></li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3><em><strong>Student Housing</strong></em></h3> 
<ul> 
 <li><strong>Location</strong>: Student Services - Student Housing Services</li> 
 <li><strong>Legal Authority</strong>:&nbsp;<em>Ryerson University Act</em>, 1977 (amended)</li> 
 <li><strong>Information Maintained</strong>: student name, number, contact information, program of study, year of study</li> 
 <li><strong>Uses</strong>: to verify student status, process residence applications, administer residence contracts, recording incidents, maintain records of non-academic discipline</li> 
 <li><strong>Users</strong>: Student Housing Services staff and Security Services in the event of a security incident</li> 
 <li><strong>Individuals in Bank</strong>: Students in residence owned by Ryerson University</li> 
 <li><strong>Retention and Disposal</strong>:&nbsp;<strong>5 years</strong></li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3><em>S<strong>tudent Non-Academic Discipline</strong></em></h3> 
<ul> 
 <li><strong>Location</strong>: Director of Student Services</li> 
 <li><strong>Legal Authority</strong>:&nbsp;<em>Ryerson University Act</em>, 1977 (amended)</li> 
 <li><strong>Information Maintained</strong>: student name, number, contact information, program of study, notes, memorandums and other documentation in connection with the allegation of non- academic misconduct</li> 
 <li><strong>Uses:&nbsp;</strong>to enable the Director of Student Services to deal informally with allegations of student non-academic conduct</li> 
 <li><strong>Users:&nbsp;</strong>Director of Student Services&nbsp;</li> 
 <li><strong>Individuals in Bank</strong>: students</li> 
 <li><strong>Retention and Disposal</strong>:&nbsp;<strong>Indefinitely</strong></li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3><em><strong>Tri Mentoring Program</strong></em></h3> 
<ul> 
 <li><strong>Location</strong>: Student Services – Tri Mentoring Program</li> 
 <li><strong>Legal Authority</strong>:&nbsp;<em>Ryerson University Act</em>, 1977 (amended)</li> 
 <li><strong>Information Maintained</strong>: student name, number, contact information, program of study&nbsp;</li> 
 <li><strong>Uses</strong>: to facilitate mentoring match and to promote program equality for participants<br> </li> 
 <li><strong>Users</strong>: Tri-Mentoring Staff</li> 
 <li><strong>Individuals in Bank</strong>: students</li> 
 <li><strong>Retention and Disposal</strong>:&nbsp;<strong>5 years</strong></li> 
</ul>
    





